</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> White/light area’s in the first 40 cm after the leading edge 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Only visible in the 1st print after handling the media. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> In most cases fingerprints or smudge is visible 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-CF0DD3D5-F0C4-4CF7-BBB3-5563E27CB4B0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional Logging (if available)</title><p class="- topic/p ">No logging available to pinpoint to this case.
</p></section><section id="GUID-548AB94F-B852-4DCB-AF43-ABB424AEF0E9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/></section><section id="GUID-9CBDEE4E-991F-4BF7-A9EC-F164BE557685" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ADAM-triggers</title><p class="- topic/p ">No available ADAM-triggers 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><p class="- topic/p "> When a media is loaded into the printer use the option (Cut long strip) to cut off the outer surface of a media roll. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Handling the media using gloves and storage in a clean environment (eg: Cardboard box) can prevent the defect from happening.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">When a media is loaded into the printer use the option (“Cut long strip”) to cut off the outer surface of a media roll. 
</p></li></ol></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">Touching the media with bare hands can leave a thin layer of skin fat. This can influence the adhesion and or the ink spreading on the media surface. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Other kind of fats/pollution can also leave a layer on the surface of the media. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-945E6C60-1212-47DF-9487-92374227D4B4.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
